BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 70.08000000000001 600 Td (Chapter 1: Why Start a YouTube Channel) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (YouTube has over 2 billion monthly active users watching content every day.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (It is the second largest search engine after Google, owned by Google itself.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (YouTube content is evergreen: videos you post today can earn views for years.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Unlike social media posts that disappear, YouTube videos compound in value over time.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (You can monetize through ads, sponsorships, products, and affiliate marketing.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (YouTube builds authority in your niche that transfers to other business opportunities.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (The platform is free to use as both a creator and a viewer.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Video builds trust and connection with audiences faster than any other medium.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Many full-time YouTubers started as a side hobby recording in their bedrooms.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (A channel with 1000 subscribers can generate meaningful income and opportunities.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (There is still massive opportunity for new creators who bring unique perspectives.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (This book will get you from zero to your first 1000 subscribers systematically.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (1) Tj ET

endstream
