BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 100.80000000000001 600 Td (Chapter 2: Choosing Your Niche) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Your niche is the specific topic your channel consistently creates content about.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Choose a niche you can create content about weekly for at least two years.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Passion matters but profitability matters too. Find the intersection of both.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Research existing channels in your topic. Competition validates demand exists.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Look for underserved angles: specific audiences, unique formats, or fresh perspectives.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Profitable niches include finance, technology, health, business, and education.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Hobby niches like cooking, gaming, crafts, and fitness build loyal communities.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Avoid being too broad. A cooking channel for busy parents beats a general food channel.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Your niche should be specific enough to attract subscribers but broad enough for content.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Study small channels \(1K-10K subs\) in your niche to see what works for starters.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (List 50 video ideas for your chosen niche. If you struggle, it may be too narrow.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (You can always adjust your niche later but starting focused helps algorithms recommend you.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (2) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
