BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 93.12 600 Td (Chapter 4: Equipment on a Budget) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Your smartphone camera is good enough to start a YouTube channel today.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Modern phones shoot in 1080p or 4K which exceeds YouTube quality requirements.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Audio quality matters more than video quality. Invest in a microphone first.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (A lavalier \(clip-on\) microphone for your phone costs 15-25 dollars and sounds great.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (The Rode NT-USB Mini is an excellent desktop microphone for about 100 dollars.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Natural window light is free and produces flattering results for talking head videos.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Position yourself facing a window with the light on your face, not behind you.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (A ring light costs 30-50 dollars and provides consistent lighting any time of day.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (A simple tripod or phone mount keeps your camera steady during recording.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Background matters: choose a clean, uncluttered area or use a simple backdrop.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Total starter budget: under 50 dollars using your phone and a clip-on microphone.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Upgrade equipment only after you have published consistently for three months.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (4) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
