BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 81.6 600 Td (Chapter 8: Thumbnail Design Secrets) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Thumbnails are the visual advertisement for every video. They must grab attention.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Use a close-up face with a clear expression: surprise, excitement, or curiosity.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Faces with emotions get significantly more clicks than thumbnails without faces.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Add three to five words of large, bold text that complements your title.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Do not repeat the exact title text. Use different words that add context.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Use high-contrast colors that stand out against YouTube's white interface.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Yellow, red, and bright green backgrounds perform well in testing.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Keep the design simple. If it is not readable at the size of a postage stamp, simplify.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Use Canva's free YouTube thumbnail templates as starting points.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Maintain a consistent style across thumbnails so your content is recognizable.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Look at your video page and ask: does my thumbnail stand out among competitors?) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (A-B test thumbnails by changing them after a few days if performance is low.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (8) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
