BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 50.879999999999995 600 Td (Chapter 10: Upload Schedule and Consistency) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Consistency matters more than frequency. One video weekly beats random uploads.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Choose a realistic schedule you can maintain for months without burning out.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Publishing on the same day and time trains your audience to expect new content.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (YouTube rewards consistent channels with more recommendations to new viewers.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Batch filming multiple videos in one session saves setup time and creates a buffer.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Film two to three weeks ahead so you always have content ready to publish.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Quality should never be sacrificed for quantity. One great video beats three mediocre ones.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Use YouTube Studio to schedule uploads in advance for consistent publish times.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Announce your schedule in your videos so viewers know when to return.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (If you miss a week, do not quit. Just publish the next scheduled video on time.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Most successful creators started with once weekly and increased as they grew.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Twelve consistent months of weekly uploads is the foundation of channel growth.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (10) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
