BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 39.360000000000014 600 Td (Chapter 11: Growing Your First 100 Subscribers) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Your first 100 subscribers are the hardest because you have no momentum yet.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Tell everyone you know about your channel: friends, family, coworkers, classmates.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Share your videos on relevant Reddit communities, forums, and Facebook groups.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Comment thoughtfully on larger channels in your niche. Do not spam links.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (People who see your helpful comments will check your channel out of curiosity.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Collaborate with other small creators for cross-promotion to each other's audiences.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Answer questions on Quora and include your video link when genuinely relevant.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Create short-form content \(YouTube Shorts\) that gets recommended more easily.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Shorts can go viral and drive subscribers to your long-form content quickly.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Optimize your channel page so first-time visitors immediately subscribe.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Ask for subscribers at the end of every video with a specific reason to subscribe.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Celebrate every milestone: first subscriber, first comment, first 10, first 50, first 100.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (11) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
