BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 108.48 600 Td (Chapter 14: Avoiding Burnout) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Creator burnout is real and has caused many talented YouTubers to quit permanently.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Set boundaries between content creation and personal life from the beginning.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Batch create content so you have a buffer and never feel behind schedule.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Take planned breaks and communicate them to your audience. They will understand.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Do not read negative comments obsessively. Most criticism is not constructive.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Avoid comparing your growth to other creators who started at different times.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Remember your original motivation for starting. Reconnect with that purpose regularly.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Delegate tasks you dislike: editing, thumbnails, or descriptions can be outsourced.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Celebrate small wins instead of only focusing on the subscriber count.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Connect with other creators who understand the unique challenges you face.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Protect your mental health. No video is worth sacrificing your well-being.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Sustainable, enjoyable creation for years beats intense burnout in six months.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (14) Tj ET

endstream
